The paper deals with link analysis in social networks using Answer set programming (ASP), which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (AI) and falls under the cs.AI category. The paper also discusses the generation of explanations, which is a topic related to machine learning (ML) and interpretability, falling under the cs.LG category. The use of domain knowledge and declarative program transformations also suggests a connection to databases (cs.DB) and logic programming (cs.SI). Finally, the application of the proposed approach to social networks indicates a connection to the cs.SOC category.
